{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE7takeRefAA0bE0VSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","text":"ObjectRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"extendedModule":"GLibObject","title":"takeRef()"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef\/takeRef()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","text":"ObjectRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In other words, this function will convert a floating reference (if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"present) into a full reference.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Typically you want to use "},{"code":"g_object_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in order to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"automatically do the correct thing with respect to floating or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"non-floating references, but there is one specific scenario where"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this function is helpful."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The situation where this function is helpful is when creating an API"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that allows the user to provide a callback function that returns a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"GObject. We certainly want to allow the user the flexibility to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"return a non-floating reference from this callback (for the case"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"where the object that is being returned already exists)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At the same time, the API style of some popular GObject-based"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"libraries (such as Gtk) make it likely that for newly-created GObject","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instances, the user can be saved some typing if they are allowed to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"return a floating reference.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Using this function on the return value of the user’s callback allows","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the user to do whichever is more convenient for them. The caller will","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"always receives exactly one full reference to the value: either the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"one that was returned in the first place, or a floating reference","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that has been converted to a full reference."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function has an odd interaction when combined with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" running at the same time in another thread on"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the same "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" instance. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" runs first then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the result will be that the floating reference is converted to a hard"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"reference. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_take_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" runs first then the result will be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that the floating reference is converted to a hard reference and an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"additional reference on top of that one is added. It is best to avoid","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this situation."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref\/takeref()"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The base object type.","type":"text"}],"title":"ObjectRef","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef/ObjectProtocol-Implementations":{"abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","title":"ObjectProtocol Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref\/objectprotocol-implementations","type":"topic"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/Object":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Object","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Object","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The base object type.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/object","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Object"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef/takeRef()":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef\/takeRef()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"title":"takeRef()","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref\/takeref()"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"abstract":[],"title":"GLibObject","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject","type":"topic","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject"}}}